    "III-D-III-E.Benchmarking Setup: We evaluate our approach using a Clearpath Jackal robot equipped with an Intel RealSense D435i RGB-D camera (RGB-only input, 69°horizontal FOV).For visualization and analysis, LiDAR data was recorded from a SICK TIM551 2D sensor.",
    "The system ran on ROS Noetic with an NVIDIA RTX 3080 GPU laptop connected to the Jackal over a local network.",
    "Depth estimation was performed in real time using TensorRT-accelerated Depth-Anything-V2 [1].",
    "Experiments were conducted in indoor environments with static cardboard boxes to simulate clutter.",
